HEADWORD: Manducus
<hw>Man*du"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>manducare</ets> to chew.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. & Rom. Antiq.)</fld>
<def>A grotesque mask, representing a person chewing or grimacing, worn
in processions and by comic actors on the stage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

